## ğŸ§  Core Skills You Must Learn

A good penetration tester understands:

âœ… Linux  
âœ… Networking fundamentals  
âœ… Web technologies  
âœ… Operating systems  
âœ… Scripting basics  
âœ… Security tools  
âœ… Problem solving  

Tools are secondary.  
Understanding systems is primary.

---

## âš¡ The Penetration Testing Workflow

Every pentest follows a structured methodology.

### 1. Reconnaissance

Gather information about the target.

```
nmap <target>
whois <domain>
dig <domain>
gobuster dir -u http://target -w wordlist.txt
```

Goal: map the attack surface.

---

### 2. Enumeration

Extract deeper information from services.

```
nmap -sC -sV <target>
enum4linux <target>
nikto -h http://target
```

Goal: identify weaknesses.

---

### 3. Exploitation

Use vulnerabilities to gain access.

```
searchsploit <service>
msfconsole
sqlmap -u "URL" --dbs
hydra -l admin -P passwords.txt ssh://target
```

Goal: prove the vulnerability is real.

---

### 4. Privilege Escalation

Gain higher access after initial compromise.

```
sudo -l
find / -perm -4000 2>/dev/null
linpeas.sh
```

Goal: move from user â†’ root/admin.

---

### 5. Post-Exploitation

Maintain access and analyze the system.

```
cat /etc/passwd
history
crontab -l
```

Goal: understand the impact.

---

