## ğŸ§  Beginner Learning Strategy

1. Learn Linux first
2. Learn networking basics
3. Understand how web apps work
4. Practice scanning and enumeration
5. Break systems in labs
6. Read writeups
7. Repeat

Consistency beats intensity.

---

## ğŸ¯ Realistic Expectations

Penetration testing is hard.

You will:

- fail often
- get stuck
- feel confused
- learn slowly

This is normal.

Skill grows with time, not shortcuts.

